Title: Sigh No More
Pairing/Group: Ryoda
Rating: PG
Warnings: Mentions of alcohol consumption.
Notes: Much love to my beta, . Written forever ago for for 2009.
Summary: Jin and Yamapi conspire to get Tatsuya and Ryo to fall in love with each other.


When Ueda Tatsuya entered KAT-TUN’s green room, he found it abuzz with conversation. That was odd in itself because it was generally empty at that time of the morning, or if anyone was there, they didn’t talk much. However, the strangest thing about it was that Akanishi Jin was a major participant in the conversation. He never arrived this early unless he was needed for something. Since KAT-TUN only had a few rehearsals much later that day, Jin’s presence was curious indeed.

The subject of their conversation was the return of Kanjani8, specifically the return of one Nishikido Ryo, who happened to be one of Jin’s best friends, as well as Tatsuya’s frequent opponent. They didn’t fight with fist (though Tatsuya would love to slug Ryo in the face) but with words, a merry war of insults and snide remarks between them. This battle had begun practically the moment the two first met, and progressed ever since. No matter how busy the two were, they always seemed to find the time for a confrontation or two. Or three. Or four. There was never a clear winner; they gave up keeping score long ago.

“Are you gonna stand there all day, hime?” Speak of the devil. Or in this case, Nishikido Ryo.

Tatsuya turned around and flashed his most charming smile at the new arrival, who was accompanied by his band mate, Yamashita Tomohisa. “I see you’re just as odious as always.”

They proceeded to stare each other down (more like glare), neither relenting until Yamapi cleared his throat loudly, prompting them to get moving or else. They both rolled their eyes as Yamapi led the way into the green room. Jin sprang up from the couch and glomped Yamapi and Ryo. The other member’s of KAT-TUN in the room, Kamenashi Kazuya and Nakamaru Yuichi, remained seated and greeted all three with a simple “good morning.”

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

Night fell and Kame, Jin, and Yamapi went out for drinks to celebrate Ryo’s return, even though the guest of honor was too exhausted to go with them. After several drinks, Jin had, what was for him a stroke of genius. His plan was so brilliant it couldn’t possibly fail, at least according to him.

His plan was this: He, Kame, and Yamapi, with the help of a few others, would get Tatsuya and Ryo together by tricking them into liking each other. After all (again according to Jin), the unresolved sexual tension between them was so thick one could cut it with a knife.

Kame and Yamapi, too drunk to argue, heartily agreed. They spent the rest of the night outlining the plan, making sure every bit was flawless.

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

The plan was put into action the next day. As Ryo walked down the hallway to NEWS’s green room, Kame and Maru (who recruited to the cause) got into position. Just as Ryo was nearing the corner, they began to talk loudly.

“Is it true? Does Tatsuya really love Nishikido-san?” Maru asked. Ryo paused.

“Yes,” Kame replied.

“Seriously?”

“He spends hours each day writing songs about him.”

“Why hasn’t he confessed?”

“Are you kidding? Nishikido-san would never let him hear the end of it. And not in a good way.”

“Poor Tat-chan.”

“He’d never admit his love anyways. You know how he is around Nishikido-san.”

“True.”

“It’s a pity, really. If he loved him back, they’d be perfect for each other.” Kame and Maru walked off, continuing their talk about Tatsuya’s “love”.
Ryo checked to make sure they were out of sight before he slid to the ground in disbelief. It couldn’t be true. It just couldn’t. Why would Ueda love him? Nevertheless, Kame and Maru seemed so very serious. Did people really think of him that way? That he’d scorn someone because they confessed their love? Well, that part was probably true, but…

Wait, did Kame say they’d be perfect for each other? Him and Ueda? It couldn’t be. Never in a million years. Yet, why did he feel so guilty? He can’t begin to imagine how their repartee must affect Ueda. To be insulted day in and day out by the one you love and still love them would make you either the strongest person alive or the most pathetic. For some reason, Ryo preferred to think the former. Ueda was anything but pathetic.

Ryo made his decision just as Tatsuya appeared.

“Your band mantes are looking for you,” Tatsuya said. “Really, why did they send me? Can’t they send someone—”

“Thank you for telling me,” Ryo interjected.

“Actually in your – wait, what?”

“You heard me.”

“Are you expecting me to believe you said – you said thank you? Thank you? To me? Are you sick? Did you finally go crazy?”

“I’m perfectly fine. Well, I must be on my way,” Ryo gave Tatsuya a dazzling smile and walked off, leaving a stunned Tatsuya staring after him in bewilderment.

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

Tatsuya wandered around the jimusho in daze. That didn’t just happen, right? He must’ve been dreaming, or maybe sick. He checked his forehead for a fever and found none. It is a trick, a prank, or maybe a twisted version of Ni no Arashi. Anything but what actually seemed to happen. Nishikido Ryo said thank you. To him. His eternal foe. Maybe he was brainwashed or replaced by an alien. Or a robot. Or maybe an alien robot.

Voices saying his name jolted him out of his reverie.

“Tatsuya, really? Are you sure?” It was Jin.

“Positive,” Yamapi replied. Tatsuya hid himself from sight and continued to eavesdrop.

“But that’s just—”

“I know! I tried to tell him Ueda-san wasn’t worth it, but he wouldn’t listen.”

“It wouldn’t be pretty.”

“It’d be terrible.”

“Tatsuya is too proud to accept his love, especially because they’ve been feuding since day one.”

Wait, Tatsuya thought, are they talking about Nishikido?

“Poor Ryo-chan. He doesn’t deserve this,” Yamapi said, as if answering Tatsuya’s silent question.

“I’m hungry,” Jin said, “Let’s go eat.” He and Yamapi walked away.

Tatsuya was even more bewildered than before, if that was possible. Were his ears working properly today? Maybe he should get them checked. However, that conversation provided a reason for Nishikido’s unusual actions earlier. If Nishikido really did love him, it all made sense. Tatsuya was horrified. How could this happen? Nishikido. Nishikido loved him and he didn’t realize it. If he had known, he wouldn’t have been so rude to him earlier. He didn’t deserve Nishikido’s love. But maybe, just maybe, he could make up for it.

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

“Do you think it worked?” Jin asked later that night. He, Kame, Yamapi and Maru had gathered at his place for some drinks.

“You should’ve seen Nishikido-san’s face! It was priceless!” Kame laughed.

“Bet it wasn’t as priceless as Ueda-san’s was,” Yamapi responded.

Jin poured everyone another round.

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

Meanwhile, back at the jimusho, Ryo was packing up his things when Tatsuya appeared in the doorway of NEWS’s green room.

“Is it true?” He said.

“Is what true?” Ryo replied.

“What they said.”

“Depends on what they said.”

“Do you really lo—” Ryo stopped his words with a kiss. It worked exceedingly well.

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

Several days passed. Several long and tedious days where Tatsuya and Ryo showed no sign of their newfound love for each other. However, that was to be expected, much to Jin’s disappointment. Therefore, he decided to stage an intervention. He called a group meeting between KAT-TUN and NEWS, meaning he invited them all out for dinner and drinks, his treat. All members accepted his offer.

Halfway through dinner, the room grew quiet as Tatsuya and Ryo were in an argument.

“I thought you loved me,” Ryo said.

“As if,” Tatsuya replied.

“Then were Kame and Maru lying?”

“I thought you loved me.”

“As if.”

“Then were Jin and Yamapi lying?”

“No one was lying,” Kame said.

“We have proof,” Yamapi added.

“WHAT?” Ryo and Tatsuya yelled.

“I found this earlier. It’s a love song, written by Ryo-chan, obviously to Tatsuya,” Jin revealed a piece of paper.

“And this is a love song written by Tatsuya, obviously to Nishikido-san,” Maru took out another piece of paper.

Ryo and Tatsuya swore.

“It seems we’ve betrayed ourselves,” Ryo said.

“That it does,” Tatsuya smiled.

And they live happily ever after.

They're all too short to be drabbles but I couldn't think of anything else to call them... Prompts taken from a list a friend posted.


 

Don’t Look

She pulls her hood further over her eyes and turns away, wishing she could melt into the shadows and reappear miles away. She doesn’t want to be here with him, the one she loves, the one who broke her heart. She musters up the courage for one last glance and their eyes meet. A tear rolls down her cheek as she runs away.

 

They’ll never know

He wraps his arms around her and pulls her in for a heated kiss. As their tongues clash, he wonders what his girlfriend’s doing. Laughing quietly to himself, he deepens the kiss.

 

I don’t get it

Why me? Why does this always happen to me? I never meant to hurt you, but I did and there’s nothing I can do to fix it.

 

Found it

Your eyes twinkle as we gaze at the sun setting over the ocean. I put my arm around your shoulders and lean in for a kiss. In the background, fireworks go off and bells ring.

 

The writing on the wall

“I’m sorry. I never meant for it to end this way. I hope that someday you can forgive me. I always loved you,” the red letters glisten as I hold your cold hand in mine.

 

What now?

I push some hair out of your sleeping face. You look so peaceful, lying there. A smile graces your lips and I kiss your forehead before slipping out the door.

Title: Algebra
Pairing: KoyaShige
Genre: AU
Rating: PG13 ((It's all Ryo's fault))
Summary: Ryo blackmails Shige into being Koyama's algebra tutor
A/N: Written forever ago for's KoyaShige stimulus and posted in honor of Shige's birthday today~

Nothing that short should look that smug. Naturally, Nishikido Ryo managed it anyways. I always knew associating with him would cause my downfall, I just never actually believed it. Oh, how wrong I was. I don’t make a habit of telling him my secrets, but he has a way of finding out the stuff you don’t want anyone else to know.


If it was any other secret, I would not hesitate to punch him in the face. Not that it would help much. But this secret is too important for that. Much too important. So I settle for begging him not to tell anyone, which only makes his smirk wider. He tells me he’ll hold his tongue (however poisonous it may be) if I do him a small favor. When I ask what it is, he just laughs. Bastard.


Which brings me to where I am now, standing on someone’s doorstep by request of Nishikido, waiting to meet the mysterious friend of his whom needs an algebra tutor. A friendly woman I assume is the mystery friend’s mother answers the door and tells me he’s, “upstairs, first door on the right.” I follow her directions and knock on the door. When I hear someone call, “Come in,” I freeze. Nishikido is a bigger bastard than I thought.


Koyama Keiichiro opens the door and looks surprised to see me. I manage to compose myself long enough to greet him and explain that Nishikido sent me. Koyama pales slightly at this, but smiles and gestures for me to enter.


I glance around the room. It appears normal enough except for the cat sprawled out on the bedspread whom Koyama introduces as Nyanta. I (grudgingly) sent a silent thank you to Nishikido for warning me to take my allergy medicine as Nyanta jumps off the bed and starts rubbing against my legs. Koyama laughs at that then proceeds to pick up the cat and set him outside the door, apologizing profusely. Whether to the cat or me, I don’t know. Now cat free, the room seems infinitely smaller. I smile nervously and set my bag down near the desk. I immediately get to work asking Koyama about what he’s having trouble with in algebra. I quickly figure out that that’s nearly everything. It takes longer than planned to finish his test corrections, so I end up staying for dinner and then for the night, sleeping in a futon Koyama’s mother laid out for me. Luckily, it’s a Friday and we don’t have school the next day.


This pattern continues for the next few months. My friends start to tease me about how much time Koyama and I spend together after the first month. Koyama’s friends welcome me with open arms and all their homework problems. Koyama tells them to back off and go find their own tutors. After two months, we’re on a first name basis. He calls me, “Shige,” and I call him, “Keii-chan.” Half of my wardrobe seems to have ended up at his house and his mother knows all of my favorite foods.


I suppose now is the time to explain why this bothers me, if it isn’t already painfully obvious. For the longest time, almost as long as I’ve known I’m bisexual, I’ve had a crush on Keii-chan. Nishikido found that out and most likely decided to make me Keii-chan’s tutor just to see me squirm with the unfairness of it. To be so close to someone you like, but not being able to do anything is a very painful experience. Nishikido knew that it would drive me insane. I’m sad to say he’s right.


It’s now May. The first of May, to be exact, and a Friday. I stand on Keii-chan’s doorstep for the nth time, clutching a box of cake which I had bought at a nearby confectionary. He’s told me a thousand times to just go inside and not bother with knock, but I don’t listen. No one answers and I vaguely recall him telling me something about his mother not being home today even though it’s his birthday. I knock again, this time he answers. He must have been in the middle of changing out of his uniform because he’s only wearing jeans that cling precariously to his hips. I avert my eyes, blushing, and stammer out a “Happy Birthday” while shoving the cake box into his hands. He smiles brightly, making me flush deeper, and thanks me.


We go to his room and set up for our study session, the need for serious tutoring disappeared long ago. Nyanta gives me a disdainful look before jumping off the bed and rubbing against my legs on his way out of the room. Keii-chan makes himself comfortable on the bed and I at his desk.


We study like this for some time, Keii-chan occasionally calling me over and asking a question when he wasn’t chattering aimlessly. Each time I savor the light brushes of my skin against his as I lean over to point out his mistakes. It seems the longer our study session lasts, the more mistakes he makes. It thrills me, yet worries me at the same time. He’s making mistakes on problems that are easy even for him.


He calls me over for the umpteenth time and before I can comprehend what’s happening, I find myself pulled onto the bed. I gape at Keii-chan, who is hovering above me, and try to ignore the textbook digging into my back. He stares at me briefly in a way that makes me shiver. I know he felt it because he smirks and suddenly he’s kissing me.


I hope it isn’t a dream. It would be too embarrassing to face him again if it is. And it feels too good. He starts kissing a trail from my earlobe down to my collarbone. I let out a loud moan, all previous thoughts of embarrassment forgotten.


The door bangs open. It’s Nishikido. Keii-chan looks over at him, not the least pit perturbed to be caught making out on his bed with another guy, his hands under said guy’s shirt. I, on the other hand, turn bright red and try to hide my face. All Nishikido does is mutter, “Finally,” and proceeds to order us to “make ourselves decent so we can go party.” Keii-chan complies, getting up and putting on a shirt from his closet. I sit up and smooth down my own clothing. As we follow Nishikido out of the door, Keii-chan whispers in my ear, saying we can leave the party early, before winking and grabbing my hand. Our fingers twine together and I consider taking him up on the offer.

Title: Denial

Pairing: Ohmiya

Genre: AU college fluff? Crack? I dunno…

Rating: PG13

Disclaimer: I have a calendar and a few posters, but otherwise Arashi doesn’t belong to me…

Summary: Nino is in denial.

A/N: Written a while ago, but I decided to post this in honor of Nino’s birthday tomorrow. My first Arashi fic so I apologize if it fails.
 

 

 

Ninomiya Kazunari, more commonly referred as Nino or, on rare occasions and to his parents, Kazu, did not have a crush on that cute guy in his art class, no matter what his dorm mate, Matsumoto Jun, might say. Not in the least. The fact that Nino had no interest in art before he saw that guy was, according to him, completely irrelevant. He only, discretely mind you, found out the guy’s name (Ohno Satoshi) because he admired his artwork. There was no other reason.

When asked what the best way to approach Ohno would be, Aiba Masaki, a friend of Nino, said to give him a puppy, which was a typical Aiba answer. Why would someone give a puppy to a college student? Aiba’s friend (and secret crush, again according to Jun), Sakurai Sho, said to ask him if he wanted to get coffee together. Nino just rolled his eyes and went back to playing games on his Nintendo DS. He never went anywhere without it, so that in cases like this, when he felt the need to tune those around him out, he would have it. He didn’t even want to think of Jun’s suggestion, which was to buy Ohno an expensive gift.

Whenever Nino tried to figure out why Ohno was so hard to talk to, he couldn’t. It wasn’t as if Ohno exuded a ‘stay away from me’ vibe. “Hell, that annoying junior high brat had an easier time talking to him, and it was obvious that he had a crush on him,” Nino thought. Nino didn’t need Jun to tell him that (He did anyways, but that’s just how Jun is). “How hard is it to strike up a conversation? It shouldn’t be this difficult…” But it was. Nino was completely baffled, although he hid it.

Jun, Sho, and Aiba spent a long time trying to convince Nino that he “needed to get it into his head that he was completely infatuated with the guy and therefore should ask him out. Preferably sooner rather than later, or else measures will have to be taken”. Nino began to berate them, but suddenly squeaked and attempted to hide behind Jun, who gave a knowing smirk as Ohno came into view and then proceeded to engage the man in a lengthy conversation about where he bought his jeans and what hand cream he used because, “your hands are gorgeous.” Blushing, Ohno rapidly greeted Nino and the others before hurrying out of sight. Nino, also blushing, gave Jun a deadly glare. Aiba and Sho stood there, clueless of what had just happened.

Later that day, Jun cornered Nino and, in his best DoS manner, threatened to smash all of his games into tiny little pieces if Nino didn’t ask Ohno out by the end of the week. Naturally, by the time Friday arrived, Nino had yet to comply. Jun was not amused. He took all of Nino’s games and hid them, leaving a note reading, “You have until sunset,” in their place.

To say Nino was very angry would be an understatement. He was royally pissed. So he decided to do what he did best. He took a load of Jun’s whites to a nearby Laundromat with the intent of washing them with a red sock.It was not one of his more devious plans, but he was too pissed to care. Especially since Jun’s favorite white shirt was in the load. As luck would have it, while he was in the middle of loading the washer, Ohno Satoshi walked in with a bag full of laundry slung over his shoulder.
Nino froze. All he could do was watch in silence as Ohno prepared the washing machine, thinking that Jun was right. Ohno’s hands were gorgeous, but not as gorgeous as his ass. Nino blinked, trying to escape from that train of thought. Since when did he go around checking out other guy’s asses?

Coming to the only conclusion he could, Nino quickly crossed the Laundromat to where Ohno stood, and tapped him on the shoulder. Ohno turned around and smiled when he recognized him saying, “Ni –”

Nino never let him finish. Instead he back Ohno up against the machine and kissed him. Ohno gasped, giving Nino the opportunity to slip his tongue into his mouth. It didn’t take long for him to respond, putting his arms around Nino’s neck and twining his fingers in his hair. Nino slid his hands down Ohno’s back and into his back pockets, confirming that his ass was indeed as amazing as it looked from across the room.

Halfway through their heated make out session, Nino remembered Jun’s clothing; however, he simply shrugged and went back to kissing Ohno senseless.

The End

Title: On ne voit bien qu'avec le coeur ~It is only with the heart that one can see rightly~
Chapter: Prologue
Pairing: Junda, Akame, TaNaka, one-sided Kokame and Maruda
Rating: Er… PG with occasional swears… something like that…
Genre: angst, romance, fluff
Summary: Ueda Tatsuya is a prince who ran away from home. While on the run, he meets Taguchi Junnosuke, an actor. Together they are wrapped into a complex love *insert polygon here*.
A/N: This is my first time writing a KAT-TUN fic. Doozo yoroshiku onegaishimasu.


Prologue

Torrential rains poured from the heavens, darkening the sky and adding to the dismal mood of the young man sitting in the window seat of his bedroom. He stared at the mobile phone in his hand, as he had been doing for the past few hours. It did not ring. It never rang. No one called him, because no one was allowed to call him, and the ones who were allowed to call him never called. An empty life for an empty man. More than once, he had wished a mysterious stranger would come and take him away from all this. Nevertheless, no one ever came.

Ueda Tatsuya, heir apparent to the throne, was desolate.

~~~~~~~~~~~~

The only words one could use to describe the apartment shard by Taguchi Junnosuke with his best friend were bachelor and pad. From the leather couch, to the big screen television, to the empty take-out boxes in the trash pin, that fact was indefeasible.

While the storm raged outside, Junno sat on the couch playing video games. He was on his fourth game of the day, having completed the previous three. There probably were better ways for him to relieve his stress, but he did not care. He had been waiting all day for a phone call and now, at almost eleven o’clock at night, he doubted that he would receive it at all.

He swore as ‘GAME OVER’ flashed across the screen. He shut off the game and went into the kitchen to heat up some cold pizza. Sitting down at the table, he sighed and resigned himself to prepare for yet another week’s worth of auditions. He thought he had done particularly well at this audition, but alas, it did not seem to be enough.

He began to wonder where his flatmate was. His work must have ended hours ago, yet he had not returned. He hated to be alone on nights like this. His fear was not as bad as it was when he was younger, but he still abhorred storms. Lightning streaked across the sky and the power went out. Suddenly, the phone rang.

~~~~~~~~~~~~

Kamenashi Kazuya was lighting candles around his apartment when he heard a knock on the door. Placing, the lighter on the kitchen counter, he went to answer it. Standing in his doorway was Akanishi Jin, soaking went and dripping onto the floor.

“Jin! You’re soaking wet!” Kame exclaimed.

“Tell me something I don’t know…” Jin grumbled, stepping inside. Kame left and reappeared with a towel and some dry clothes. Jin accepted them gratefully.

“Why are you here?” Kame asked when Jin was mostly dry.

“The photo shoot took longer than expected,” Jin replied.

“Why didn’t your manager drive you home?”

“She had a big date. I didn’t want her to be later than she already was.”

“Sometimes you’re too nice, Jin.”

“I know.”

The two men sat in silence for several minutes until Kame spoke up. “As long as you’re here do you want to help me go over my lines?”

Jin smiled, “That’s right. You start filming soon, don’t you?”

“They still need to cast one more person, but I heard that would be decided today.”

“I can’t believe you’re starring in a drama. It seems like only yesterday you were just an extra.”

“That was yesterday.”

“Oh.”

Kame rolled his eyes, “It’s been a while since we had time to chat like this, ne?”

“Yeah, we’ve both been so busy lately.”

“Tell me about it…”

“Sometimes I feel like I should take a vacation.”

“Lucky you. I won’t have any free time for months.”

“You sure are popular lately. I mean, ever since the break-up—”

“Never ever mention that again! I don’t need to be constantly reminded of it! It’s always ‘I’m sorry to heat about the break-up’ or ‘You were such a cute couple. What went wrong?’ I don’t need your, or anyone else’s, pity, thank you very much!” Tears were streaming from Kame’s eyes as he said this, and they eventually turned into sobs.

Jin wrapped his arms around the younger man, and Kame sobbed into his shirt. Suddenly, everything was quiet. Kame had cried himself to sleep.

~~~~~~~~~~~~

Tanaka Koki lounged on the couch in the den of his penthouse apartment. He had bought the apartment when his third album went platinum. Now his friend, Nakamaru Yuichi, sat sideways in a nearby armchair, his legs draped over an arm.

“Don’t tell me you’re still bitter about that guy?” Maru asked.

Koki didn’t answer.

“This is a chance for you to make up for your mistakes. Claim it was just a phase and find a nice girl,” Maru said.

Koki snorted. “Like you’re one to talk. We all know you’re secretly pining after him,” he said with venom.

Maru blushed, “How do you know—”

“It’s so obvious, it makes me sick. No wonder you never show your face at court.”

“I didn’t know anyone knew,” Maru said softly.

No one said anything after that.

~~~~~~~~~~~~

At noon the next day, a maid knocked on the door of Tatsuya’s room.

“Your highness, would you like me to bring you lunch in your room?” she asked. When no one answered, the maid opened the door. She noticed the doors that led to the balcony were open. She quickly searched the room and found it empty.

She ran from the room screaming.

~~~~~~~~~~~~

A/N: Thank you for reading! Hopefully, you aren't horribly confused. Comments are greatly appreciated. Many thanks to my beta,
kiwi_starlight
 .
